President Obama has declared a major disaster in Minnesota due to severe storms and flooding that occurred in March 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures in various counties. Paul J. Ricciuti has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.